The paper presents a novel wavelet driven deep neural network for mechanical fault diagnosis, which involves feature learning and nonlinear mapping. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
